        <abstract> 
<p>Sends some examples of <hi rend="italic">Gentiana</hi> that he thinks may shed light on the origin of double flowers. Since specimens grew in sterile soil their double flowering cannot be attributed to excess food. CD advances the hypothesis that some change in natural conditions causes sterility, which then causes compensatory development of petals, the organs closest in morphology to those whose functions have been checked.</p> 
        </abstract>
